data.description: Well-known local act, Spitune, in 'duo' formation playing both covers and originals. Both weird/gnarly and sublime. They have also been described as a comedy act. Technically not true, but when these dudes get going the comedy just kind of happens. As a matter of fact, you never know what's going to happen.
'Silk and smoke' vocals. Like, for real. Brad croons out the best hits of the 60s through today.
Original classical guitar pieces that could easily pass for Bach etudes.
You came for the 90s covers, but you left floating on original love songs.

Local virtuoso's Bronwyn Bird (Nyckelharpa), Justin Nawn (Guitar), Daniella Fischetti (Violin) & Tim Ryan (Upright Bass) forge the ornate sounds of strings with gripping rhythms and pure foot stomping energy. Nawn & Bird run the "Birdhouse Center for the Arts." Daniella & Tim perform with "Pyrenesia" & "Hub Hollow." Pinball wizards of their art, it doesn't matter if you never get a chance to play. Just watch and learn. Folk, Bluegrass, New Grass, Old Time, Scandinavian.
Duo specializing in sweet vocal harmonies. Endless breadth of music, but the Beatles, Dead, and Simon and Garfunkel covers are something special.
Original acoustic duo featuring bluesy vocals, rhythmic guitar and eclectic horns.
Solo alt folk originals. Eerily beautiful.
Obscure hits and deep cuts played on ukulele. You'll be like, "That song's familiar. Who sings that again?"

Soulful and groovy, it's a great choice for all occasions. This is modern rock (think Black Keys, Heartless Bastards) brined in blues and dusted with psychedelia. Krysta Kowalchik's vocals pierce through a heavy rhythm section, while Jim White's vintage keyboard sounds add thickness and vibe.

Sam Steffen is a Philadelphia-based singer-songwriter whose songs are the torch-wood for a new generation of folk music that has learned from the best stuff in the tradition, and that aims, in spite of everything, to keep the human spirit alive and kicking. A versatile musician and skilled finger-picker, Sam is at heart a story-teller, and a prolific one, with more than six studio albums.

The Swiss Guard has been making loud music for quiet people since 2018. With singer/songwriter/guitarist Justin Pope, guitarist Brian Green, bassist Evan Straley, keyboardist Steve Thomas, and Ryan Whittemore on drums, TSG delivers all the feels you’re lookin’ for. As fitting a band of restless players rooted in jazz, folk, punk, and pop, The Swiss Guard grabs your ear, pulls at your heart, and offers company you didn’t know you needed. Pairs well with Tom Waits, Leonard Cohen, and Belle and Sebastian.

Little Flowers is a dreamy bedroom folk / indie pop duo with members Brian Dale Allen Strouse of The Lawsuits and songwriter Thérèse Anne. Absolutely beautiful songwriting. The debut EP “Glitter” was released November of 2019. They are currently recording their follow up single, due to drop early 2021.
